---
title: Salonized web development workshop
---

<div class="container-fluid readme"
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">

            <section class="readme-section">
                <h2 class="readme-header">Setting up</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go on your Desktop and create a new <strong>folder</strong> named <code>retreat-memories</code></li>
                    <li>Open your text editor, and open that folder. Then go ahead and do the following:</li>
                    <li>
                    In Sublime Text left navigation:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Right click <strong>"New file"</strong></li>
                        <li>Save it as <code>index.html</code> with <strong>Cmd + S</strong> or <strong>Ctrl + S</strong></li>
                        <li>Do the same to create a <code>style.css</code> file</li>
                        <li>Then <strong>"New Folder"</strong> and create an <code>images</code> folder</li>
                    </ul>
                    </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Finally double click on <code>index.html</code> to open it with Chrome</li>
              </ol>
            </section>

            <section class="readme-section">
                <h2 class="readme-header">Add some content to your page</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Start with this HTML code in <code>index.html</code></li>
                </ul>

                <% code("html") do %>
                    <html>
                      <head>
                        <meta charset="utf-8">
                        <title>My own retreat memory book</title>
                      </head>
                      <body>
                        <h1>This is a header, very important text</h1>
                        <p>This is the important line everyone reads..</p>
                        <p>
                          <a href="#">This is a link</a>
                        </p>
                    
                        <img src="#" alt="picture description" width="100">
                      </body>
                    </html>
                <% end %>
            </section>

            <section class="readme-section">
                <h2 class="readme-header">CSS, adding some style.</h2>
                <p>Link your stylesheet <code>style.css</code> in the <code>head</code> section of your HTML</p>
                <% code("html") do %>
                    <head>
                      <link href='style.css' rel='stylesheet'>
                    </head>
                <% end %>
                <p>Then copy/paste the CSS code below in <code>style.css</code> and <strong>fix it</strong> cause it's ugly</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>For fonts use <a href="https://www.google.com/fonts" target="_blank">Google Fonts</a></li>
                    <li>You can find nice colors on <a href="https://coolors.co/" target="_blank">Coolors</a> or <a href="https://colorhunt.co/" target="_blank">Color Hunt</a></li>
                </ul>
                <% code("css") do %>
                    /* style.css */
                    body{
                      background: rgb(245,245,245);
                      color: green;
                      font-size: 25px;
                      font-family: Helvetica;
                    }
                    h1{
                      font-family: Courier;
                      color: red;
                      font-weight: lighter;
                      font-size: 10px;
                    }
                    h2 {
                      font-family: Courier;
                      color: pink;
                      font-weight: lighter;
                      font-size: 8px;
                    }
                    a {
                      color: yellow;
                    }
                    a:hover {
                      text-decoration: none;
                      color: purple;
                    }
                    <% end %>
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/12NUbkX6p4xOO4/giphy.gif">
                    </div>
            </section>
            <section class="readme-section">
                <h2 class="readme-header">Wrap with <code>div</code> and add a footer</h2>
                <p>Wrap different sections in different <code>div</code></p>
                <p>Go ahead, get creative and have fun!</p>
                <div class="image-container">
                    <img src="https://media2.giphy.com/media/3Fi5jZkZdJA4M/source.gif">
                </div>
            </section>
</div>